F.4.1 — Footer reactive pinned by 6 unit cases
----------------------------------------------------------------
test/components/footer-reactive.test.ts
  - baseline render without subscription
  - status.update{context_usage.percent=50} → context: 50.0% + 1 requestRender call
  - status.update{model='kimi-k2-5'} → Footer model field updates
  - session_meta.changed{patch:{title:'my plan'}} → requestRender triggered
  - disposer clears both subscriptions (subsequent events no-op)
  - status.update with NaN percent → renders 0.0%, no NaN propagation

Interactive pty smoke (seeing live % change during a real turn) by
design is out-of-band on macOS (no coreutils timeout) — unit coverage
above pins every branch the live path exercises.


F.4.2 — --session / -r / -S picker routing
----------------------------------------------------------------
$ node apps/kimi-cli/dist/index.mjs --session --print -p hi
error: --session without an id requires shell mode.
(exit 1; grep -c "requires shell mode" == 1)

$ node apps/kimi-cli/dist/index.mjs -S --wire
error: --session without an id requires shell mode.

$ node apps/kimi-cli/dist/index.mjs -r --print -p hi
error: --session without an id requires shell mode.

$ node apps/kimi-cli/dist/index.mjs --session sesX --print -p hi
error: failed to start print mode: Session "sesX" not found under
       /Users/moonshot/.kimi/sessions.
(id with value flows through print mode — no picker-mode false positive)


